2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 153
BY SENATOR MCMATH
A RESOLUTION
To commend Madison Elizabeth Hogan on being crowned the 100th Miss St. Tammany
Parish Fair Queen.
WHEREAS, Madison Hogan is the reigning 2025-2026 St. Tammany Parish Fair
Queen; and
WHEREAS, Madison, the 2025-2026 Fair Queen, is a resident of Mandeville,
Louisiana, and a proud graduate of Mandeville High School; and
WHEREAS, at only 22 years old, Madison holds a Bachelor of Science degree in
Finance with a minor in economics from Southeastern Louisiana University; and
WHEREAS, she is a Southeastern Louisiana University Double Legacy Scholar and
an alumni of Alpha Omicron Pi sorority and the Gamma Beta Phi Society; and
WHEREAS, Madison competed on the Southeastern Louisiana University College
of Business finance competition team and also served as an ambassador for the SELU
College of Business; and
WHEREAS, she is a loyal volunteer for Our Daily Bread food pantry, and has been
a volunteer on Project Prom, a nonprofit started by her mother which provides free prom
dresses to high school students who are unhoused, in foster care, or otherwise in need of
support; and
WHEREAS, Madison's goal is to attend law school and pursue a career in contract
law; and
WHEREAS, she currently works for the St. Tammany Parish Clerk of Court finance
department; and
WHEREAS, during Madison's one-year tenure with the St. Tammany Parish Fair,
she has served as the spokesperson and representative for the fair, making special
appearances and performing philanthropic work; and
WHEREAS, in January 2026, as Fair Queen, Madison competed at the Louisiana
Association of Fairs and Festivals for the title of LAFF Queen, representing the St.
Tammany Parish Fair and placing in the top ten in a competition of over sixty fair and
